were receiving

00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:52.200
care that was confusing,
conflicting, dispiriting,

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:54.840
and included medical errors.

00:02:54.840 --> 00:02:57.487
They also reported substantial
financial distress,

00:02:57.487 --> 00:02:59.070
despite health
insurance coverage that

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:00.586
was supposed to protect them.

00:03:00.586 --> 00:03:03.210
So we're going to take a closer
look at the poll results today.

00:03:03.210 --> 00:03:05.940
We'll also talk about some
of the less obvious costs

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:08.640
of serious illness, costs
that don't necessarily

00:03:08.640 --> 00:03:11.702
appear on medical bills but
still make it hard for people.

00:03:11.702 --> 00:03:13.660
And we want talk about
some possible solutions,

00:03:13.660 --> 00:03:15.384
so it won't all
be doom and gloom,

00:03:15.384 --> 00:03:17.550
including programs that our
panelists are working on

00:03:17.550 --> 00:03:19.510
to try to address these issues.

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:21.846
So first, let's watch a
clip from the US Department

00:03:21.846 --> 00:03:23.220
of Health and
Human Services that

00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:27.950
brings home the financial
impact of serious illness.

00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:29.660
