diagnosed was very good.

00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:35.960
I was running my own business.

00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.620
I was president of a
Boys and Girls Club.

00:03:38.620 --> 00:03:42.900
1996, I went to get
some life insurance.

00:03:42.900 --> 00:03:48.080
I had the blood work, urine
test, and I was rejected.

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:53.010
And as it turned out, I had
impending kidney failure.

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:58.324
My kidneys continued to
deteriorate until 2004,

00:03:58.324 --> 00:03:59.615
when they shut down completely.

00:03:59.615 --> 00:04:02.090
I went to the emergency room.

00:04:02.090 --> 00:04:03.580
I began dialysis.

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:08.020
I was 51, 2006, when
I had my transplant.

00:04:08.020 --> 00:04:09.670
I had an amazing recovery.

00:04:09.670 --> 00:04:11.920
I was taking immunity
suppressant medication

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:13.970
that was fairly expensive.

00:04:13.970 --> 00:04:16.209
I am looking at a couple
hundred dollars a month

00:04:16.209 --> 00:04:18.260
copay, even with Medicare.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:21.490
And first I have to pay for
the deductible every year.

00:04:21.490 --> 00:04:24.010
I probably won't retire,
and one of the reasons

00:04:24.010 --> 00:04:26.540
is because of the cost
of the medications

00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:29.170
that I will constantly
have to pay for.

00:04:29.170 --> 00:04:32.320
The fact that the government
is looking at the cost of drugs

00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:32.890
is a plus.

00:04:32.890 --> 00:04:35.030
I'm very encouraged by that.

