00:33:58.660 --> 00:34:00.911
this very vulnerable population.

00:34:00.911 --> 00:34:02.410
The other thing I
just wanted to say

00:34:02.410 --> 00:34:05.860
is that we've been now 20
years into a cycle of consumer

00:34:05.860 --> 00:34:09.434
information and transparency
that would somehow allow people

00:34:09.434 --> 00:34:11.350
to make good choices and
create the incentives

00:34:11.350 --> 00:34:12.760
for organizations.

00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:15.489
And many people are starting
to conclude that that's not

00:34:15.489 --> 00:34:18.280
a successful strategy, or
at least not sufficient

00:34:18.280 --> 00:34:20.449
to solve some of these problems.

00:34:20.449 --> 00:34:22.929
So what we have now is
people with insurance

00:34:22.929 --> 00:34:26.440
facing high deductibles,
facing ruinous costs.

00:34:26.440 --> 00:34:28.179
And that's colliding
with a system that

00:34:28.179 --> 00:34:31.449
has consolidated where costs
are escalating dramatically

00:34:31.449 --> 00:34:33.969
where the prices are
really out of control

00:34:33.969 --> 00:34:36.440
because there's no
counter negotiating power.

00:34:36.440 --> 00:34:39.780
And from a policy level, that's
