in particular make it
difficult for family and others

00:35:15.580 --> 00:35:16.630
to provide coverage.

00:35:16.630 --> 00:35:19.240
So there was a
lot of information

00:35:19.240 --> 00:35:22.330
in this survey about caregivers,
about the financial stresses

00:35:22.330 --> 00:35:23.710
that we saw in Bob's slide.

00:35:23.710 --> 00:35:26.230
But also just how hard it
is emotionally for them

00:35:26.230 --> 00:35:28.850
and how much work it is to
care for their relatives.

00:35:28.850 --> 00:35:30.970
And so I'm curious what
thoughts you guys have

00:35:30.970 --> 00:35:34.359
about that, about what we could
do better for those people.

00:35:34.359 --> 00:35:35.650
ERIC SCHNEIDER: I'll just say--

