00:36:10.594 --> 00:36:12.010
ROBERT MASTER:
Again, some lessons

00:36:12.010 --> 00:36:14.440
from the Medicaid world.

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:18.280
Medicaid really was our
nation's first long-term care

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:21.250
and disability insurer
for support care.

00:36:21.250 --> 00:36:25.816
And maybe it is the
only comprehensive one.

00:36:25.816 --> 00:36:27.610
One of the most
important supports

00:36:27.610 --> 00:36:29.260
was personal care assistance.

00:36:29.260 --> 00:36:31.090
Self-directed personal
care assistance,

00:36:31.090 --> 00:36:33.070
which was a unique
Medicaid benefit that

00:36:33.070 --> 00:36:38.020
grew up over decades, and,
at in least in the more

00:36:38.020 --> 00:36:42.280
recent iterations that Toyin
and I have been involved in,

00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:44.020
was the opportunity
to essentially

00:36:44.020 --> 00:36:47.020
have family members, whether
it's a spouse, whether it's

00:36:47.020 --> 00:36:51.610
a daughter, son, granddaughter,
grandson, nephew, neighbor,

00:36:51.610 --> 00:36:56.500
friend, be that
caregiver and reimbursed.

00:36:56.500 --> 00:36:59.000
And you say, well,
how can you do that?

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.150
Well, in some ways, how
can you not do that?

00:37:01.150 --> 00:37:05.920
Because the cost of having
some reasonable reimbursement

00:37:05.920 --> 00:37:09.640
for that kind of support
is the alternative

00:37:09.640 --> 00:37:13.000
to a skilled nursing
facility in many cases.

00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:15.370
Or worse, for many
frail elders, more

00:37:15.370 --> 00:37:18.640
of a long-term nursing facility
at several hundred dollars

00:37:18.640 --> 00:37:20.230
a day.

00:37:20.230 --> 00:37:24.980
And so are the lessons
from the Medicaid world?

00:37:24.980 --> 00:37:27.490
And historically,
Medicaid was always

00:37:27.490 --> 00:37:32.225
viewed as the marginalized
twin to Medicare.

00:37:32.225 --> 00:37:36.660
But in fact, has been this
engine of policy innovation.

00:37:36.660 --> 00:37:37.950
And that's a good example.

00:37:37.950 --> 00:37:41.970
And is that applicable to
the more broad and general

00:37:41.970 --> 00:37:42.910
population?

00:37:42.910 --> 00:37:43.590
MARGOT SANGER-KATZ:
