00:48:44.690 --> 00:48:48.140
They still may have problems,
but certainly they're

00:48:48.140 --> 00:48:50.900
not just sort of abandoned
on the street, uninsured

00:48:50.900 --> 00:48:54.932
using public facilities
if they do that.

00:48:54.932 --> 00:48:56.390
ROBERT MASTER: Just
to add, I think

00:48:56.390 --> 00:49:00.490
the ACA has been an
unmitigated blessing

00:49:00.490 --> 00:49:03.800
and it has a long way to go.

00:49:03.800 --> 00:49:09.860
But if we add to what
talking about with people

00:49:09.860 --> 00:49:12.439
with preexisting
conditions, in the ACA

00:49:12.439 --> 00:49:14.480
there was a provision for
the Center for Medicare

00:49:14.480 --> 00:49:16.250
and Medicaid Innovation.

00:49:16.250 --> 00:49:18.300
And substantially funded.

00:49:18.300 --> 00:49:21.530
And a good example of
the kind of innovations

00:49:21.530 --> 00:49:24.620
were really very, very
relevant to the populations

00:49:24.620 --> 00:49:26.620
that we're talking about.

00:49:26.620 --> 00:49:29.480
And that example
