back and forth, back and forth,

00:49:40.560 --> 00:49:44.150
back and forth to the hospital
because the system just wasn't

00:49:44.150 --> 00:49:46.410
organized for their care.

00:49:46.410 --> 00:49:50.570
And in fact, many of the
issues of hospital care

00:49:50.570 --> 00:49:55.820
made things worse in terms
of drug-resistant organisms

00:49:55.820 --> 00:49:59.870
and the like, and transitions
for skilled nursing facilities.

00:49:59.870 --> 00:50:03.800
And so the idea of could we
take a pre-identified population

00:50:03.800 --> 00:50:06.680
with complex chronic
illness, low thresholds

00:50:06.680 --> 00:50:10.190
to these hospitalizations, and
think about a different path

00:50:10.190 --> 00:50:10.850
for them.

00:50:10.850 --> 00:50:12.590
And it started out
a different path

00:50:12.590 --> 00:50:16.160
through the emergency room,
and maybe an infirmary bed.

00:50:16.160 --> 00:50:19.610
But where it evolved in the
second iteration in 2014,

00:50:19.610 --> 00:50:22.370
and this is just one
example, is maybe

00:50:22.370 --> 00:50:23.960
we don't need to
hospitalize them

00:50:23.960 --> 00:50:27.470
at all if we can put all the
components of hospital care

00:50:27.470 --> 00:50:30.980
at home for this frail elder
and think about what that

00:50:30.980 --> 00:50:33.470
does to the transitions
and all of the risks

00:50:33.470 --> 00:50:34.940
around transitions.

00:50:34.940 --> 00:50:38.120
And that, again, is
the kind of thing

00:50:38.120 --> 00:50:40.220
that did not happen
systematically

00:50:40.220 --> 00:50:42.320
prior to the ACA.

00:50:42.320 --> 00:50:47.480
And the benefits will not
accrue on any scale maybe

00:50:47.480 --> 00:50:49.280
for another five to eight years.

00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:52.820
But I am predicting a Medicare
bundled payment for a hospital

00:50:52.820 --> 00:51:00.060
at home DRG then is
paid to hospital today

00:51:00.060 --> 00:51:04.140
and the potential transfer of
substantial numbers of patients

00:51:04.140 --> 00:51:07.170
that are on our
medical floors today

00:51:07.170 --> 00:51:10.370
to home-based care in
a handful of years.

00:51:13.497 --> 00:51:15.580
TOYIN AJAYI: Yeah, I
